properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 10 at 2:42PM MST until January 11 at 4:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...HIGH WINDS RETURNING TO WIND PRONE AREAS TONIGHT THROUGH
SATURDAY...

* WHAT...West winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 65 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County, North
Snowy Range Foothills, South Laramie Range and South Laramie
Range Foothills.

* WHEN...From 11 PM this evening to 4 PM MST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Travel will be difficult for light and high profile
vehicles. High risk of truck blowovers on interstates.
properties.instruction:
For the latest road closures and conditions in Wyoming, go to
wyoroad.info or dial 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 11 PM THIS EVENING TO 4 PM MST SATURDAY
